\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs44 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. \
Prepare Chocolate Wafer Crust (recipe below).\
In a large bowl, whisk together the condensed milk, key lime juice, egg yolks, sugar, lime zest, vanilla extract and salt. Spoon filling into warm crust. Bake the pie until the filling is set, about 12 minutes.\
Transfer the pie to a \cf2 cooling rack\cf0  and let stand for 20 minutes at room temperature.  When the pie is completely cool, decorate with milk chocolate curls. Store wrapped or in an airtight container, in the refrigerator.\
