\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl460\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs44 \cf3 {\listtext	\'95	}28 chocolate wafer cookies\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl460\sa180\ql\qnatural
\cf3 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.\
Spin the cookies and sugar in a food processor until fine crumbs. Then drizzle in the butter, pulsing to combine. Press this mixture firmly and evenly into the bottom, up the sides of a 9-inch pie pan.\
Bake on the middle rack of the oven until crust is set and appears dry,   about 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and cool completely, about 1 hour.}